LazySysAdmin

Target IP: 192.168.186.36

Scanning



There are six TCP ports open on the target machine.

Enumeration

Ports 139 and 445: SMB

The target machine has an SMB share called share$ open. This share contains interesting files. I connected to the SMB share and downloaded the files to my local machine. This share also contains the WordPress files.


I downloaded the wp-config.php file on my machine. This file contains the username and password Admin:TogieMYSQL12345^^. Before using this, I wish to enumerate further to find out more about the target.


The different files contain the contents above. The deets.txt file contains the password 12345. The todolist.txt contains an important information about the web application. And the robots.txt contains more information about the directories.

Port 80: HTTP

The webpage above is displayed for this application.

Performing a basic scan using the command gobuster dir -u http://192.168.186.36/ -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -x php,html,txt shows the result above. It looks like the target is running a WordPress application too.


The robots.txt file contains a few entries. The entry /Backnode_files/ contains the files for this web application, such as the images and scripts.


The WordPress application displays the webpage above. A possible username togie appears. There is also the admin user too. Doing a code-review shows the target is running WordPress 4.8.1 version of the application.

Exploitation


Using the login Admin:TogieMYSQL12345^^ I obtained from the SMB share share$ wp-config.php file, I managed to gain access to the WordPress application.


I replaced the twentysixteen theme's 404.php file with PHP Pentest Monkey reverse shell script. I fired up a listener on port 8443.


And I obtained my reverse shell connection from the target machine by browsing to http://192.168.186.36/wordpress/wp-content/themes/twentysixteen/404.php. Now I have a foothold on the machine.

Privilege Escalation


I noticed there is another user called togie. From previous enumeration, I found the password 12345 inside the file deets.txt. After trying this password against togie, I got success.


I spawned a root shell as togie can run all commands with sudo.

The local.txt and proof.txt and flag contents after I gained a root shell.
